title: AWS
short_description: AWS SecureX Relay provides direct insight into cloud environment.
description:
**AWS SecureX Relay provides direct insight into cloud environment.**

![AWS Relay](https://github.com/CiscoDevNet/tr-05-aws-vpc-logs/blob/main/screenshots/aws-vpc.png)

**Dashboard Tiles**

- Infrastructure Summary
- Overall VPC Flows
- EC2 Instance Details
- IAM Login Users
- IAM API Users

**Threat Response**

Dynamically identify traffic flows for cloud instances and provide capability for dynamic host isolation.
tips:
**Create an IAM account with programmatic access using the following reference:**

[AWS Credential Generation](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/general/latest/gr/aws-sec-cred-types.html#access-keys-and-secret-access-keys)

**Ensure Created API Credentials Have the Following Permissions**

```
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "VisualEditor0",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "iam:GenerateCredentialReport",
        "ec2:DescribeInstances",
        "ec2:DeleteTags",
        "ec2:DescribeTags",
        "ec2:CreateTags",
        "logs:DescribeLogStreams",
        "ec2:DescribeSecurityGroups",
        "s3:ListAllMyBuckets",
        "logs:GetLogEvents",
        "iam:ListUsers",
        "apigateway:GET",
        "ec2:ModifyInstanceAttribute",
        "ec2:DescribeSubnets",
        "iam:GetCredentialReport",
        "iam:ListAccessKeys"
      ],
      "Resource": "*"
    }
  ]
}
```

**Publish Flow Logs to CloudWatch Using the Below Reference:**

[AWS VPC Logs to CloudWatch](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/vpc/latest/userguide/flow-logs-cwl.html)

configuration_spec.label: Cloudwatch Log Group Name
configuration_spec.tooltip: Log group configured for collection VPC flow logs

configuration_spec.label: Region
configuration_spec.tooltip: AWS region in which VPC resides. Example: "us-east-1"

configuration_spec.label: Desired Time Zone
configuration_spec.tooltip: Time zone for events. Example: "Pacific Standard Time"

configuration_spec.label: Days Back To Search
configuration_spec.tooltip: How many days would you like your investigations to evaluate logs for in increments of one. Be aware that too many days back can severely impact performance of module.

configuration_spec.label: Maximum Total Flows
configuration_spec.tooltip: **Optional** sets the maximum threshold for events to be considered from most recent looking back to include the total ingress and egress traffic.

configuration_spec.label: Maximum Ingress Flows
configuration_spec.tooltip: **Optional** sets the maximum threshold for events to be considered from most recent looking back to include the total ingress traffic. Please note that if this is configured along with the maximum flows option, the returned events will be no greater than the maximum flows.

configuration_spec.label: Maximum Egress Flows
configuration_spec.tooltip: **Optional** sets the maximum threshold for events to be considered from most recent looking back to include the total ingress traffic. Please note that if this is configured along with the maximum flows option, the returned events will be no greater than the maximum flows.

configuration_spec.label: AWS Address Space
configuration_spec.tooltip: **Optional** comma separated subnets in CIDR notation to denote the private AWS address space. This helps to speed up the lookup process by removing the need to dynamically capture the configured IP space every time. Please note, that if defined, the dynamic lookups will not take place, so if improperly set, may result in inconsistent data. Example: "192.168.35.0/24,10.0.0.0/8""
